# System Service – Bug Tracking Application

This service manages all system-level master and reference data used across the Bug Tracking Application and is fully configuration-driven with admin-only access.

## Overview (Single-Line Points)

1. Centralized system module for all master/reference data.
2. Admin-only service secured using Admin JWT authentication.
3. Eliminates hard-coded enums by using database-driven masters.
4. Manages project configuration masters (technologies, databases, languages, types).
5. Controls bug classification masters (types, severities, priorities, statuses).
6. Defines complete bug workflow lifecycle and transitions.
7. Implements role-based access control (RBAC).
8. Supports granular permission management.
9. Maps roles to default permission sets.
10. Supports project-specific roles (not global roles).
11. Uses soft-delete strategy to preserve audit history.
12. Ensures severity and priority are independent dimensions.
13. Enforces workflow rules via permissions.
14. Drives all UI dropdowns dynamically from master data.
15. Designed for scalable, extensible microservice architecture.

## System APIs Summary

- Project Technologies, Databases, Programming Languages
- Project Types and Industries
- Bug Types, Severities, Priorities, Statuses
- Bug Status Transitions (workflow rules)
- User Roles, Permissions, Role-Permission Mappings  
(All APIs support Create, Get, Update, Soft Delete and are ADMIN-only)

