## Core Design Principles

- Severity represents technical impact; Priority represents business urgency.
- Developers can resolve bugs but cannot close them.
- QA or Project Managers verify and close bugs.
- All deletes are soft deletes to preserve history.
- Roles are assigned per project, not globally.
- Workflow transitions are permission-driven.
- System is fully extensible without code changes.
- Master tables control UI behavior and validation.

